'''Jeremy Alberto Arévalo Mera''' (born 19 March 2005) is a [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for German {{German football updater|Stuttgart}} club [[VfB Stuttgart]]. Born in Spain, he plays for the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
===Racing Santander===
Born in [[Maliaño]], [[Cantabria]] to Ecuadorian parents, Arévalo was a [[Racing de Santander]] youth graduate. He made his senior debut with [[Rayo Cantabria|the reserves]] at the age of 16 on 8 January 2022, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 3–0 [[Segunda División RFEF]] away loss against [[CD Laredo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.periodicofiltracion.es/articulo/deportes/rayo-cantabria-pierde-3-laredo-sufre-primera-derrota-domicilio-segunda-rfef/20220108233754001958.html|title=El Rayo Cantabria pierde 3–0 contra el Laredo y sufre su primera derrota a domicilio en Segunda RFEF|trans-title=Rayo Cantabria lose 3–0 against Laredo and suffer their first away defeat in ''Segunda RFEF''|publisher=Filtr@ción|language=es|date=8 January 2022|accessdate=13 August 2023}}</ref>

Arévalo was handed his first start on 15 October 2022, and scored the winner in a 1–0 away success over [[Bergantiños FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticias/el-rayo-cantabria-vence-al-bergantinos-futbol-club-en-as-eiroas-0-1|title=El Rayo Cantabria vence al Bergantiños Fútbol Club en As Eiroas (0–1)|trans-title=Rayo Cantabria defeat Bergantiños Fútbol Club at the As Eiroas (0–1)|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=15 October 2022|accessdate=13 August 2023}}</ref> On 3 December, he scored a brace in a 2–0 win at Laredo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldiariocantabria.publico.es/articulo/deportes/ha-nacido-estrella-jeremy-arevalo/20221204111447126807.html|title=Ha nacido una estrella: Jeremy Arévalo|trans-title=A star is born: Jeremy Arévalo|publisher=El Diario Cantabria|language=es|date=4 December 2022|accessdate=13 August 2023}}</ref>

Arévalo made his professional debut on 12 August 2023, replacing goalscorer [[Aritz Aldasoro]] late into a 4–0 [[Segunda División]] home routing over [[SD Eibar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2023/08/12/64d7ba3246163f1a048b4584.html|title=El Racing arrolla a un desconocido Eibar|trans-title=Racing run over an unknown Eibar|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=12 August 2023|accessdate=13 August 2023}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 2 January 2026, Jeremy Arévalo signed a five-and-a-half-year-deal with [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2526/vfb-verpflichtet-jeremy-ar--valo-/|title=VfB sign Jeremy Arévalo|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=2 January 2026|accessdate=2 January 2026}}</ref> He made his club debut eight days later, in a 4–1 [[Bundesliga]] victory over [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].

==International career==
Eligible to play for [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] or [[Spain national football team|Spain]], Arévalo represented the latter at [[Spain national under-18 football team|under-18 level]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticias/racinguista-jeremy-convocado-seleccion-espanola-sub-18|title=El racinguista Jeremy, convocado por la Selección Española Sub-18|trans-title=The ''racinguista'' Jeremy, called up to Spain under-18 national team|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=11 April 2023|accessdate=13 August 2023}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador U20]]s for the [[2025 South American U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecuavisa.com/deportes/futbol-internacional/lista-convocados-seleccion-ecuador-sudamericano-sub20-venezuela-MF8557718|title=Esta es la lista de convocados de Ecuador para el Sudamericano Sub 20 en Venezuela|trans-title=This is the Ecuador's roster for the South American U-20 Championship in Venezuela|publisher=[[Ecuavisa]]|first=Fernando|last=Guevara|date=5 January 2025|language=es}}</ref> He was called up to the senior [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]] for a set of friendlies in November 2025.<ref>{{cite instagram |user=latriecu |postid=DQzTyENDjWk |title=¡Tenemos nuestros convocados para enfrentar a 🇨🇦 y 🇳🇿! |date=8 November 2025 |access-date=8 November 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

